dct_title_s: Part of Asia Minor to illustrate the route of W. Ainsworth, Esqr
dct_description_sm: Includes inset map of Eregli (Heraclea Pontica) and its harbor [scale ca. 1:32,000]. Buildings, ruins, fishing stations, and Chísh Depeh village and light house are shown. Mr. Ainsworth's route is colored red. Relief shown by hachures. From: Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 9 (1839), pp. 216-76; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.9 1839.
dct_publisher_sm: London : published for the Journal of the Royal Geographical Society, by J. Murray, Albemarle Street, 1839.
